text: I want to find everyone involved in this project and do some truly horrible things to them. I am a huge Sherlock Holmes fan and I am not taking this as a joke. It's an insult. To Arthur Conan Doyle and his legacy, to the huge cultural impact Sherlock Holmes has had, and to the fans of the great detective.  But even ignoring my instinctual, murderous hatred for this and everyone in it, it seems objectively awful. At least Scary Movie parodies tried to be funny, this was so cringe-worthy it was almost physically painful. Was the script written by 8 year olds? That seems to be the target audience at least, judging by the pitiful attempts at humour.

text: If you are a true Holmes fan, check out these... "The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes (1984‚Äì1985), The Return of Sherlock Holmes (1986‚Äì1988), The Case-Book of Sherlock Holmes (1991‚Äì1993) and The Memoirs of Sherlock Holmes (1994), collectively known as Sherlock Holmes, are a series of adaptations of Arthur Conan Doyle's Sherlock Holmes stories which were produced by Granada Television and originally broadcast by ITV in the United Kingdom. The series starred Jeremy Brett as Holmes and David Burke (in the Adventures series) and Edward Hardwicke (Return, Case-Book, Memoirs) as Dr. Watson."      If you are a Holmes and Watson fan, these are a must see.  Jeremy Brett (now deceased) was awesome as Holmes.  These episodes are based on each one of the stories as written by Arthur Conan Doyle and done with the quality you expect for a British production.  And yes there was a parody with Michael Caine and Ben Kingsley called "Without a clue" that was really funny.  It came out in 1988.  Much better I'm sure than these two clowns!!!

text: I get the impression someone had the idea of these actors for these characters... then didn't bother with a script.  Why?  If this was competent, it could be great.  Like 2 sequels and maybe another trilogy great.  But someone said "Nah, let's spend all our money on period clothing and no money on a script."  I mean, the villain actually sends a note telling Holmes his name and plan!  I don't think we'll be pleasantly surprised to find Holmes discovers (or bumbles into discovering) that the notes' a red herring.  I think Sony just didn't bother to hire anyone who has ever read a mystery story, let alone a Holmes story.  This is a labor of "I don't want to do any real work," not a labor of love, and thus DOA I fear.

text: Having been dumb enough to see this in the cinema when it came out, I can say that this is, without a doubt, the most terrible movie I have ever seen or that I believe has ever existed. It is a criminally shameless cash grab that was created with the sole intention of stealing money from the pockets of unsuspecting movie goers. At least other terrible movies produce some sort of enjoyment due to the fact that they are so bad... However, there was not a single second of this movie that involved something of merit, enjoyment or anything that resembled comedy in any way. It was clearly created without an inch of effort, and feels as though it was written within the space of an hour and filmed in the space of a day. Everyone involved in the creation of this movie should be absolutely completely and utterly ashamed that they were involved in such a horrifically disgusting abomination. Please, I beg of you, no one buy this movie on any streaming service or on blue ray/DVD. You will be giving your hard earned money to literal scam artists - this movie is literally a scam in itself.

text: At least it looks nice. It's colorful, the costumes look great, the sets are rich and detailed with complex lighting, gorgeous footage of London and a decent trailer (Filled with awful jokes, but that's not the trailer's fault. Biggest fault is using "The Boys Are Back In Town") And even though it's a total disgrace to the original character, I'm willing to accept that Will Ferrell plays Holmes, giving it the benefit-of-the-doubt and because I kinda like the idea of a Sherlock Holmes comedy--it makes the stories less dry.  But yeah, I don't need to tell you how awful this movie is.
